
                                            It’s understood residents are protesting against illegal land invasion.

                                         CAPE TOWN - Police have confirmed a violent protest has broken out along the Golden Highway near Finetown in the south of Johannesburg. At least three cars have been torched. It’s understood residents are protesting against illegal land invasion. The JMPD's Wayne Minnaar said: “There’s a possibility that it is over illegal land invasion in the area as there have been some removals there today.” There's a violent protest near Finetown, where 3 trucks have been torched on the Golden Highway between R550 and Link Rd. M.M pic.twitter.com/KGm4u98Y8e 